      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Here are the results for the paper **\"Compression Represents Intelligence Linearly\"** by Yuzhen Huang et al., published at **COLM 2024**:\n\n## Paper Overview\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The paper is authored by Yuzhen Huang, Jinghan Zhang, Zifei Shan, and Junxian He, from The Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and Tencent."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "It was accepted to COLM 2024."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Key Findings\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors find that LLMs' intelligence — reflected by benchmark scores — almost linearly correlates with their ability to compress external text corpora."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Their findings suggest that compression efficiency, as an unsupervised metric derived from raw text corpora, serves as a reliable evaluation measure that is linearly associated with the model capabilities."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Motivation\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "There is a belief that learning to compress well will lead to intelligence. Recently, language modeling has been shown to be equivalent to compression, which offers a compelling rationale for the success of large language models (LLMs)."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Despite such appealing discussions, little empirical evidence was present for the interplay between compression and intelligence."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Methodology\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The authors examine the relationship between compression and intelligence in the context of LLMs, treating LLMs as data compressors. They adopt the average downstream benchmark scores as a surrogate for \"intelligence\", specifically targeting knowledge and commonsense, coding, and mathematical reasoning. Across 12 benchmarks, the study brings together 31 public LLMs that originate from diverse organizations."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "They focus on three key abilities: knowledge and commonsense, coding, and mathematical reasoning, and collect new corpora from Common Crawl, GitHub, and Arxiv, respectively."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Results\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "On experiments across 31 public LLMs and 12 diverse benchmarks, they uncover a remarkable finding: LLMs' downstream ability is almost linearly correlated with their compression efficiency, with a Pearson correlation coefficient of around -0.95 for each evaluated domain of intelligence."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": " "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Notably, this linear relationship even extends to most individual benchmarks as well."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### Resources\n\n- **ArXiv**: [2404.09937](https://arxiv.org/abs/2404.09937)\n- **OpenReview**: [SHMj84U5SH](https://openreview.net/forum?id=SHMj84U5SH)\n- **GitHub**: [hkust-nlp/llm-compression-intelligence](https://github.com/hkust-nlp/llm-compression-intelligence)\n- "
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "The repo includes the compression corpora used in the paper, the code to compute compression efficiency, as well as the compression corpora collection and processing pipelines."
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "\n\n### About the First Author\n\n"
      },
      {
        "citations": [],
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Yuzhen Huang is a PhD student (since February 2024) in the Department of CSE at HKUST. He completed his undergraduate degree in Computer Science at Shanghai Jiao Tong University (2019–2023)."
      }
    ],
